    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_3310357945" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3310357945" />
    <a title="Marsha James" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106162405-marsha-james"><img alt="Marsha James" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576853599p2/106162405.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3310357945?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marsha James" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marsha James" href="/user/show/106162405-marsha-james">Marsha James</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3310357945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11206209691814206822">There&apos;s a lot of tell-tale issues about Trump and his Presidency, more so in this book. For someone like me who doesn&apos;t get involved in politics and the issues pertaining to it, I was intrigued and amused. <br/><br/>They have coined Trump to be a leader who has a psychological disorder, a racist, and a President with limited intelligence. But why is this happening? What is Hanna&apos;s basis for Trump&apos;s incompetency? In this book, we will hear a lot about what Trump has said, what he has done, and what clinica</span>
  <span id="freeText11206209691814206822" style="display:none">There's a lot of tell-tale issues about Trump and his Presidency, more so in this book. For someone like me who doesn't get involved in politics and the issues pertaining to it, I was intrigued and amused. <br /><br />They have coined Trump to be a leader who has a psychological disorder, a racist, and a President with limited intelligence. But why is this happening? What is Hanna's basis for Trump's incompetency? In this book, we will hear a lot about what Trump has said, what he has done, and what clinical psychologists think about his behavior. <br /><br />What Trump has said, pertaining to the borders set up in America: <br />- “We have people coming into the country or trying to come in — we’re stopping a lot of them. You wouldn’t believe how bad these people are. These aren’t people, these are animals.” <br /><br />What Trump has done: <br />- pro-Israel lobbying<br />What clinical psychologist thinks about his behavior? <br />- Trump has been variously described by numerous clinical psychologists — with one of them stating “we have an ethical responsibility to warn the public about Donald Trump‘s dangerous mental illness” — as suffering from a mental pervasive disorder characterized by aggression, egomania, cheating, grandiosity, instability, lying, narcissism, self-interest, and stealing. <br /><br />Scary! However, it’s scarier knowing that all 63,000,000 voted for this man. <br /><br />Has America lost their sh*t? Do we still have hope? What might be our future if we allow ourselves to be smitten by a man who is unstable and incompetent?</span>
  <a data-text-id="11206209691814206822" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


