<div id="review_3273471518" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3273471518" />
    <a title="Linda Young" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106429540-linda-young"><img alt="Linda Young" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575635440p2/106429540.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3273471518?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda Young" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda Young" href="/user/show/106429540-linda-young">Linda Young</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3273471518" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12000435910982501257">This book grabbed me by the ears and said, &quot;Hey, get ready for a thrilling ride, and oh, by the way, don&apos;t plan on sleeping tonight cause you’re going to be busy,&quot; and I totally was.<br/><br/>The plotlines are strong enough to give you a hint of the road ahead, but subtle enough that almost 3/4 through the book, I was thinking, &quot;How in the world does that first line fit in here? Did William Hanna forget about it?&quot; I like to think that I can sniff out a plot, even though I suspected you had me second-guess</span>
  <span id="freeText12000435910982501257" style="display:none">This book grabbed me by the ears and said, "Hey, get ready for a thrilling ride, and oh, by the way, don't plan on sleeping tonight cause you’re going to be busy," and I totally was.<br /><br />The plotlines are strong enough to give you a hint of the road ahead, but subtle enough that almost 3/4 through the book, I was thinking, "How in the world does that first line fit in here? Did William Hanna forget about it?" I like to think that I can sniff out a plot, even though I suspected you had me second-guessing myself. I loved the characters and can easily see all of them have parts in future books, well, except for the bad guys, but then again, I guess they won't be making any appearances. <br /><br />If you love the political, covert, and characters that can beat some A@#, then click that BUY button. <br /><br />If you like Lee Child, Brad Thor, W.E.B. Griffin, then you will like this. There aren't many authors who can spin a story that makes me finish the book in less than two days, but this can, and now you can add William Hanna to the list! If the future books are as good, then his name will be all over the place like the previous authors I mentioned. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12000435910982501257" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
