<div id="review_3310350842" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3310350842" />
    <a title="Kimberly Edwards" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106439828-kimberly-edwards"><img alt="Kimberly Edwards" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575652937p2/106439828.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3310350842?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kimberly Edwards" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kimberly Edwards" href="/user/show/106439828-kimberly-edwards">Kimberly Edwards</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3310350842" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11907507281288939843">What I love about Hanna&apos;s creativity is how he integrated all the issues surfacing the world into the life of a journalist, Mike Walker. He creatively connects these events, ideas, and situations to his life, and made him the person responsible for making a change in people&apos;s mindsets and values. <br/>He used his skills and courage to express his thoughts and opinions about the world&apos;s depressing issues that need to change. In hindsight, Mike knew this would endanger his career and even his life. How</span>
  <span id="freeText11907507281288939843" style="display:none">What I love about Hanna's creativity is how he integrated all the issues surfacing the world into the life of a journalist, Mike Walker. He creatively connects these events, ideas, and situations to his life, and made him the person responsible for making a change in people's mindsets and values. <br />He used his skills and courage to express his thoughts and opinions about the world's depressing issues that need to change. In hindsight, Mike knew this would endanger his career and even his life. However, he believes that with awareness and educating people, he can make things better for all! In connection, he has become a threat to the illegal operation of some institutions, and he is now being subject to surveillance. <br /><br />Moreover, during the surveillance, it was said that the person in charge of Mike's case took his time carefully hiding a pinhole camera in the bedroom and another in the lounge; replacing wall sockets with ones that doubled as transmitter audio listening devices; installing a tap on the landline telephone, and downloading files including contact and banking details from Walker’s computer onto a USB Flash Drive. It took less than half an hour to install intrusive access to every aspect of Walker’s private life. This was the cost of his vision to help and reach out to people. <br /><br />Meanwhile, this method of intrusive surveillance operation is illegal as stipulated in Article 8 of the European Convention on Human Rights." In the UK an authorization for the use of intrusive surveillance can only be granted by the Home Secretary, a chief constable, the Director of the Serious Organised Crime Agency (SOCA), or another designated official from SOCA, designated officials from HM Revenue and Customs, and the chairman of the Office of Fair Trading. <br /><br />The person granting the authorization may only do so if he/she considers the authorization is necessary for the interests of national security to prevent or detect serious crime, or in the interests of the economic well-being of the country. But does it matter? Do we still have the right to our privacy these days? <br /><br />Surveillance or not, we have been robbed of this right. Social Media and other forms of technology have continued to sweep away our information from the past, the present, and even the future. The hope of humanity seems bleak; however, if we educate ourselves, think with clarity, and proceed with caution, we can protect ourselves. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11907507281288939843" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


