<div id="review_3310342066" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3310342066" />
    <a title="Michelle Campbell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106438581-michelle-campbell"><img alt="Michelle Campbell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575651034p2/106438581.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3310342066?book_show_action=true">Apr 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michelle Campbell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michelle Campbell" href="/user/show/106438581-michelle-campbell">Michelle Campbell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3310342066" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7483157152253604613">Although a novel, the situation of every nation, ethnicity, and race mentioned here is true. I began to research about Myanmar and the Rohingya refugees, and it was sickening! William Hanna wrote that: &quot;According to the UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR), more than 723,000 Rohingya Muslim men, women, and children had so far fled to Bangladesh with estimates of at least 18,000 women and girls raped, 116,000 beaten, and 36,000 thrown into fires. Those who suffered most were the women and girls who bore the</span>
  <span id="freeText7483157152253604613" style="display:none">Although a novel, the situation of every nation, ethnicity, and race mentioned here is true. I began to research about Myanmar and the Rohingya refugees, and it was sickening! William Hanna wrote that: "According to the UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR), more than 723,000 Rohingya Muslim men, women, and children had so far fled to Bangladesh with estimates of at least 18,000 women and girls raped, 116,000 beaten, and 36,000 thrown into fires. Those who suffered most were the women and girls who bore the mental scars of shocking sexual violence, pregnancy as a result of rape, and the duress of a forced hazardous journey". <br /><br />And what I learned from my research is that: "Every day, around the world, 507 women and adolescent girls die from pregnancy and childbirth complications in emergency settings " (from: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.independent.co.uk/">https://www.independent.co.uk/</a>). Are these women receiving help from the government? As I continued my research, I became more shocked at the reality that these women are not receiving any medical and financial assistance, in addition, they are being trafficked to Malaysia for marriage, while rape and domestic violence is an ongoing issue. If I had not read this book, I would not realize the degree of suffering that these women are facing. <br /><br />Furthermore, it's not only the women who are suffering but the entire group! It dawned on me that this has been an issue since 1991 to the present, and their situation is still the same. So, to me, Hanna did a fantastic job by writing a book that helps humanity become more aware of these issues. <br /><br />This awareness will help many people suffering from injustice and oppression. A must-read for all! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7483157152253604613" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


