  <span id="freeText9383122103690494505" style="display:none">"The Grim Reaper" by William Hanna is a story of awareness! It teaches humanity about the impact of oppression, a dangerous leader/president, and the hatred and brutality of people toward each other. In the religious aspect and for some spiritual, it enables us to see how we have not truly practiced the edicts of what we believe in. <br /><br />It makes us realize the hypocrisy of our belief and helps influence us to make that change. In regards to the leadership of President Trump the book exposes how his ideology on building a wall to the southern US border to prevent the entry of asylum seekers and immigrants whom he claims are AIDS-ridden aliens, gang member animals, dangerous criminals, drug and people traffickers, rapists, and murderers are dehumanizing. <br /><br />It is also shocking to know that 63,000,000 Americans voted for him, which means there are a lot of likeminded white American xenophobic zealots, including Neo-Nazis and white supremacists who hate and fear people of color. <br /><br />The "socio-political" impact and social awareness that I have gained from reading this book were what stood out for me! The story is also quite interesting because it integrates the life of a journalist who shared his experience about some of the countries he visited, the situation they were in, and how he used his power as a journalist to expose the oppression that they faced. <br /></span>
