  <span id="freeText5838517635166486512" style="display:none">Politics has always been the dirtiest game that every Politician play, and it's loathed with propaganda that intends to delude us! As John Pilger, Australian journalist and award-winning documentary filmmaker shared: <br /><br />“The major western democracies are moving towards corporatism. Democracy has become a business plan, with a bottom line for every human activity, every dream, every decency, and every hope. The main parliamentary parties are now devoted to the same economic policies — socialism for the rich, capitalism for the poor — and the same foreign policy of servility to endless war. This is not democracy. It is to politics what McDonalds is to food.” <br /><br />Isn’t that true? However, we are not aware of this ploy that they play. We have become victims, and we have forgotten the real meaning of democracy. And as Hanna digs deeper on that issue, we get to see more of the truth that has been withheld from us for the longest time. <br /><br />I like how William Hanna was able to point out a lot of topics that are important to realize and ponder on the damages that it has set upon every individual, the nation, and the world! This is a book that reaches out to us, and if we listen, it will change how we respond to the issues and finally make it a UNIVERSAL RESPONSIBILITY. <br /><br /></span>
