              <span id="reviewTextContainer3310355885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14136017439207256599">How depressing are the truths being exposed from this book &quot;Grim Reaper&quot; by William Hanna! At the same time because of how deeply moving the issues shared, it makes people realize what they need to do to live responsibly, share the hope for a better world for all of humanity, and choose the best leaders to help build a better world. It&apos;s not rocket science! It&apos;s about having that courage to stand up for what you believe in, act, and influence people. <br/><br/>The issues in politics and the hypocrisy of p</span>
  <span id="freeText14136017439207256599" style="display:none">How depressing are the truths being exposed from this book "Grim Reaper" by William Hanna! At the same time because of how deeply moving the issues shared, it makes people realize what they need to do to live responsibly, share the hope for a better world for all of humanity, and choose the best leaders to help build a better world. It's not rocket science! It's about having that courage to stand up for what you believe in, act, and influence people. <br /><br />The issues in politics and the hypocrisy of politicians are something that Hanna puts a lot of emphasis on. In connection, the issue in Myanmar and the refugees who has faced a devastating cruelty was raised. They were forced to evacuate because of the campaign dubbed “Operation Clean up and Beautiful Nation.” In addition, if the American government were called upon to intercede about this issue, the President would probably start by asking the UN Security Council to take immediate action to end the violence against Myanmar's Rohingya. <br /><br />This would be followed by Vice President Mike Pence with his pointless address to the Security Council on peacekeeping reform and accusing the Myanmar military of reacting to attacks on government outposts with appalling savagery. Furthermore, Pence would give hollow assurances of swift action being taken to help the Rohingya Muslims by the administration: an administration which incidentally had imposed a travel ban on Muslims titled “Protecting the Nation from Foreign Terrorist Entry into the United States.” <br /><br />How could this be real? The hypocrisy and the lies must stop and it's time for humanity to choose the best leaders who care. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14136017439207256599" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

