<div id="review_3795794788" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3795794788" />
    <a title="Valery" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4013735-valery"><img alt="Valery" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1480691033p2/4013735.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3795794788?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Valery" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Valery" href="/user/show/4013735-valery">Valery</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3795794788" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer65510627954085369">The Grim Reaper by William Hanna combines the vagaries and political backdrop of war with a compelling narrative and story. Freelance correspondent, Mike Walker is the main character, one concerned with ethnic cleansing taking place all over the world. It becomes his mission to bring this practice to the forefront, while creating a storm of controversy and turmoil in his wake. Soon he comes under the surveillance of various governments, and perhaps he has reported just one report too many. On ma</span>
  <span id="freeText65510627954085369" style="display:none">The Grim Reaper by William Hanna combines the vagaries and political backdrop of war with a compelling narrative and story. Freelance correspondent, Mike Walker is the main character, one concerned with ethnic cleansing taking place all over the world. It becomes his mission to bring this practice to the forefront, while creating a storm of controversy and turmoil in his wake. Soon he comes under the surveillance of various governments, and perhaps he has reported just one report too many. On many levels this is a political commentary wrapped in a novel. Nonetheless you can't help but become immersed in the story, while acknowledging the horrors that are war. The author has created a meaningful book, one that certainly resonates with you if have an ounce of compassion. Great attention to detail is prevalent throughout the book, along with historical facts. Characters are well described too. Overall, a quite substantive and compelling read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="65510627954085369" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


