<div id="review_3305673572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3305673572" />
    <a title="Donna Perez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106437214-donna-perez"><img alt="Donna Perez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575648925p2/106437214.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3305673572?book_show_action=true">Apr 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna Perez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna Perez" href="/user/show/106437214-donna-perez">Donna Perez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3305673572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11121381571107589565">Excellent, intelligently written thriller.<br/><br/>Initially, I found the beginning of the book disjointed and hard to follow. Some scenes from a country to another were being introduced quickly, which I found made it hard for me to get connected to the story.<br/><br/>Fortunately, the story progresses quickly and kept me engaged until the end. Mr. William Hanna plotting is superb - some of the best I&apos;ve found in contemporary novels. I know some readers were worried about his move into more straightforward politic</span>
  <span id="freeText11121381571107589565" style="display:none">Excellent, intelligently written thriller.<br /><br />Initially, I found the beginning of the book disjointed and hard to follow. Some scenes from a country to another were being introduced quickly, which I found made it hard for me to get connected to the story.<br /><br />Fortunately, the story progresses quickly and kept me engaged until the end. Mr. William Hanna plotting is superb - some of the best I've found in contemporary novels. I know some readers were worried about his move into more straightforward political fiction, but I think his books are atmospheric and haunting - this one, in particular, was both of those things, and so political fiction or not, the ambiance is the same. Brilliant. <br /><br />This is a great novel - one that is not all that far from the possibilities of reality - and one that keeps you turning the pages until the final one. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11121381571107589565" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


