        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3305677496" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2447785106322166910">Extremely well-written. It draws you in from page one.<br/><br/>This is the kind of book I like a lot. It&apos;s fiction, so the author can make a diamond out of coal if he or she is talented enough. But this story kept me glued to it. If you like tales of political intrigue with a war journalist, different parts of the globe, and dangerous bad guys, and saving people, then I think you will like this story. I generally read a pretty good amount of nonfiction, and if it is well-written and the story is remarkab</span>
  <span id="freeText2447785106322166910" style="display:none">Extremely well-written. It draws you in from page one.<br /><br />This is the kind of book I like a lot. It's fiction, so the author can make a diamond out of coal if he or she is talented enough. But this story kept me glued to it. If you like tales of political intrigue with a war journalist, different parts of the globe, and dangerous bad guys, and saving people, then I think you will like this story. I generally read a pretty good amount of nonfiction, and if it is well-written and the story is remarkable enough, I will enjoy it more than fiction. I do try to intersperse some great fiction in there too so I don't get too bogged down reading about economics of our times or the history of man's inhumanity to man, not that there's anything wrong with reading those, but they can be a little dusty at times.<br /><br />My highest possible recommendations!<br /></span>
